ipal manager\n|leader_name            = Kurt Forsman\n|leader_title1          = \n|leader_name1           = \n|leader_title2          = \n|leader_name2           = \n|leader_title3          = \n|leader_name3           = \n|established_title      = \n|established_date       = \n|established_title2     = \n|established_date2      = \n|established_title3     = \n|established_date3      = \n|extinct_title          = \n|extinct_date           = \n|area_urban_km2         = \n|area_metro_km2         = \n|population_metro       = \n|population_blank1_title  = \n|population_blank1        = \n|population_density_metro_km2 = \n|population_urban       = \n|population_density_urban_km2 = \n|population_note        = \n|finnish_official       = \n|swedish_official       = 1\n|sami_official          = \n|urbanisation           = \n|unemployment           = \n|blank1_name            = \n|blank1_info            = \n|blank2_name            = \n|blank2_info            = \n|blank3_name            = \n|blank3_info            = \n|blank4_name            = \n|blank4_info            = \n|coordinates_type       = \n<!-- latNS=N and longEW=E set by default -->\n<!--{{Coord|59|55|15|N|20|54|35|E|region:FI_type:city(296)_scale:50000|display=title}}-->\n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|55.2|N|020|54.5|E|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m            = \n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              = \n|website                = [http://www.kokar.ax/ www.kokar.ax]\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''K\u00f6kar''' ({{Audio|K\u00f6kar.ogg|<small>pronunciation</small>|help=no}}) is an [[island]] municipality to the south-east of the [[\u00c5land]] [[archipelago]], [[Finland]].\n\nIt is also one of the [[municipalities of Finland|municipalities]] of \u00c5land. It is reachable by boat from [[L\u00e5ngn\u00e4s]] on \u00c5land or from [[Galtby]] with access to [[mainland Finland]].\n\nThe municipality has a population of {{Formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|K\u00f6kar}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name=\"population_count\"/><!-- defined by template:Infobox Finnish Municipality --> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/total area|K\u00f6kar}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/waters area|K\u00f6kar}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population density|K\u00f6kar|round=2}}|PD/km2}}.\n\nThe municipality is unilingually [[Finland-Swedish|Swedish]].    \nThe natural reserve of \u00d6stra L\u00e5ngsk\u00e4r is located there. Other notable islands include Kyrkog\u00e5rds\u00f6.\n\n[[Ulla-Lena Lundberg]], a [[Sweden Finns|Finnish]] author, was born in K\u00f6kar in 1947.\n\n==History==\nK\u00f6kar was first inhabited over 3,000 years ago by seal hunters. A [[Franciscan]] [[monastery]] was founded in Hamn\u00f6 in the 15th century. Today the monastery is in ruins. The church dedicated to [[St. Anne]] was built in 1784 in the place of the old monastery church.\n\n==Sights==\n\n[[Image:Franciskanergrav p\u00e5 K\u00f6kar, h\u00f6sten 1990..jpg|thumb|left|170px|The grave of a Franciscan monk on the side of the church of St. Anne]]\n\n'''The church of St. Anne''' was built in the site of the old monastery church during the reign of king [[Gustav III of Sweden|Gustav III]] and is located on the island of Hamn\u00f6. It is next to the ruins of the monastery. The clocktower was built in the 19th century. The clocktower had to be restored after an Autumn storm damaged it in 1978. A model of a sailing ship hangs in the church. It was given by a local sailor who had been captured by [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[pirate]]s but who later managed to escape. The model has 64 [[cannon]]s.\n\n'''The local museum''' was opened in 1988 and its purpose is to show how the people of K\u00f6kar lived in the 19th century and onwards to the 1940s. The now museum building, built in 1913, used to be an old school.\n\nThere is also '''a [[Bronze Age]] site''' dating back to 1150\u20131050 BC. It was found in 1918.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|K\u00f6kar}}\n*[http://www.kokar.ax/ Municipality of K\u00f6kar] \u2013 Official website {{in lang|sv}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090706091306/http://www.kokarmuseum.fi/ The museum of K\u00f6kar's web site]\n\n{{\u00c5land Islands topics}}\n{{Municipalities of \u00c5land}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kokar}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of the \u00c5land Islands]]\n[[Category:Finnish islands in the Baltic]]\n[[Category:Landforms of the \u00c5land Islands]]\n\n\n{{\u00c5land-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Finnish Municipality\n|name                   = K\u00f6kar\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|K\u00f6kar kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = K\u00f6kar.vaakuna.svg\n|shield_size            = \n|image_blank_emblem     = \n|blank_emblem_type      = \n|blank_emblem_size      = \n|image_map              = K\u00f6kar.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of K\u00f6kar in [[Finland]]\n|image_dot_map          = \n|dot_mapsize            = \n|dot_map_caption        = \n|dot_x =  |dot_y = \n|pushpin_map            =Finland \u00c5land Islands\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in \u00c5land Islands\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 250\n|province               = {