ern Ostrobothnia]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The municipality has a population of {{formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/total area|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/waters area|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population density|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki|round=2}}|PD/km2}}. Neighbour municipalities are [[Haapaj\u00e4rvi]], [[Haapavesi]], [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]], [[Pyh\u00e4nt\u00e4]] and [[Siikalatva]].\n\nThe name ''K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki'' means literally \"snout hill\".\n\nThe municipality is unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n==Nature==\nMost common soil type is [[till]].\n\nOver 60% of area is [[swamp]]. Bigges swamps are K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4enneva, Lauttaneva, Onkineva and Vellihonganneva.\n\n[[Pyh\u00e4joki (river)|Pyh\u00e4joki]] river flows through municipality.\n\n==Villages==\n* [[Venetpalo]]\n* [[Kirkonkyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Miiluranta]]\n* [[Ojalehto]]\n* [[Alajoki]] \n* [[Porkkala, K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki|Porkkala]]\n* [[Rannankyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Saviselk\u00e4]]\n* [[Syd\u00e4nmaankyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Venetpalo]]\n* [[Pyrr\u00f6nper\u00e4]]\n\n==Notable people==\n*[[Berndt Leonard Frosterus]] \n*[[Aappo Luomajoki]] \n*[[Markku Koski]] \n*[[Kalevi Hemil\u00e4]]\n*[[Paula Vesala]] \n*[[Matti Ristinen]]\n*[[Sasu Paavola]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category-inline|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.karsamaki.fi/}} {{in lang|fi}}\n\n{{NorthernOstrobothnia}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karsamaki}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of Northern Ostrobothnia]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1869]]\n[[Category:1869 establishments in the Russian Empire]]\n\n\n{{OuluProvince-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the district of Turku|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki, Turku}}\n{{Infobox Finnish municipality\n|name                   = K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki\n|official_name          = {{lang|fi|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4en kunta}}<br />{{lang|sv|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = Paanukirkko.jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki Church ({{lang|fi|Paanukirkko}})\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki.vaakuna.svg\n|shield_size            = \n|image_blank_emblem     = \n|blank_emblem_type      = \n|blank_emblem_size      = \n|image_map              = K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki in [[Finland]]\n|image_dot_map          = \n|dot_mapsize            = \n|dot_map_caption        = \n|dot_x =  |dot_y = \n|pushpin_map            = <!-- name of a location map as per Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|province               = [[Oulu Province]]\n|region                 = [[Northern Ostrobothnia]]\n|subregion              = Nivala\u2013Haapaj\u00e4rvi sub-region\n<!-- Smaller parts (e.g. boroughs of a city) and seat of government -->\n|seat_type              = \n|seat                   = \n|parts_type             = \n|par