province]] of [[Oulu (province)|Oulu]] and is part of the [[Northern Ostrobothnia]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The municipality has a population of {{formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/total area|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/waters area|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population density|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki|round=2}}|PD/km2}}. Neighbour municipalities are [[Haapaj\u00e4rvi]], [[Haapavesi]], [[Pyh\u00e4j\u00e4rvi]], [[Pyh\u00e4nt\u00e4]] and [[Siikalatva]].\n\nThe name ''K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki'' means literally \"snout hill\".\n\nThe municipality is unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n==Nature==\nMost common soil type is [[till]].\n\nOver 60% of area is [[swamp]]. Bigges swamps are K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4enneva, Lauttaneva, Onkineva and Vellihonganneva.\n\n[[Pyh\u00e4joki (river)|Pyh\u00e4joki]] river flows through municipality.\n\n==Villages==\n* [[Venetpalo]]\n* [[Kirkonkyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Miiluranta]]\n* [[Ojalehto]]\n* [[Alajoki]] \n* [[Porkkala, K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki|Porkkala]]\n* [[Rannankyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Saviselk\u00e4]]\n* [[Syd\u00e4nmaankyl\u00e4]]\n* [[Venetpalo]]\n* [[Pyrr\u00f6nper\u00e4]]\n\n==Notable people==\n*[[Berndt Leonard Frosterus]] \n*[[Aappo Luomajoki]] \n*[[Markku Koski]] \n*[[Kalevi Hemil\u00e4]]\n*[[Paula Vesala]] \n*[[Matti Ristinen]]\n*[[Sasu Paavola]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commonscat-inline|K\u00e4rs\u00e4m\u00e4ki}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.karsamaki.fi/}} {{in lang|fi}}\n\n{{NorthernOstrobothnia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karsamaki}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of Northern Ostrobothnia]]\n[