{"title_page": "Kumlinge", "text_new": "{{Infobox Finnish municipality\n|name                   = Kumlinge\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|Kumlinges kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = File:Kumlinge-Kyrkan fr\u00e5n \u00f6ster.JPG\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Kumlinge Church\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = Kumlinge.vaakuna.svg\n|shield_size            = \n|image_blank_emblem     = \n|blank_emblem_type      = \n|blank_emblem_size      = \n|image_map              = Kumlinge.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of Kumlinge in [[Finland]]\n|image_dot_map          = \n|dot_mapsize            = \n|dot_map_caption        = \n|dot_x =  |dot_y = \n|pushpin_map            =Finland \u00c5land Islands\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in \u00c5land  Islands\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 250\n|province               = {{flag|\u00c5land}}\n|region                 = \u00c5land\n|subregion              = Archipelago sub-region\n<!-- Smaller parts (e.g. boroughs of a city) and seat of government -->\n|seat_type              = \n|seat                   = \n|parts_type             = \n|parts_style            = <!-- =list (for list), coll (for collapsed list), para (for paragraph format)\n                               Default is list if up to 5 items, coll if more than 5-->\n|parts                  = <!-- parts text, or header for parts list -->\n|p1                     = \n|p2                     = <!-- etc. up to p10: for separate parts to be listed-->\n|government_footnotes   = \n|leader_title           = Municipal manager\n|leader_name            = Christian Dreyer\n|leader_title1          = Chairman of municipality council\n|leader_name1           = Mats Per\u00e4maa\n|leader_title2          = Chairwoman of municipality executive board\n|leader_name2           = Gun-Mari Lindholm\n|leader_title3          = \n|leader_name3           = \n|established_title      = \n|established_date       = \n|established_title2     = \n|established_date2      = \n|established_title3     = \n|established_date3      = \n|extinct_title          = \n|extinct_date           = \n|area_urban_km2         = \n|area_metro_km2         = \n|population_metro       = \n|population_blank1_title  = \n|population_blank1        = \n|population_density_metro_km2 = \n|population_urban       = \n|population_density_urban_km2 = \n|population_note        = \n|finnish_official       = \n|swedish_official       = 1\n|sami_official          = \n|urbanisation           = \n|unemployment           = \n|blank1_name            = \n|blank1_info            = \n|blank2_name            = \n|blank2_info            = \n|blank3_name            = \n|blank3_info            = \n|blank4_name            = \n|blank4_info            = \n|coordinates_type       = \n<!-- latNS=N and longEW=E set by default -->\n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|15.5|N|020|46.7|E|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m            = \n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              = \n|website                = [http://www.kumlinge.ax/ www.kumlinge.ax]\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Kumlinge''' is a [[municipalities of Finland|municipality]] consisting of a group of [[island]]s in [[\u00c5land]], an [[autonomous]] territory of [[Finland]]. Kumlinge, which is also the name of the largest island in the group, means \"rocky passage.\"\n\nThe municipality has a population of {{formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|Kumlinge}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name=\"population_count\"/><!-- defined by template:Infobox Finnish Municipality --> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/total area|Kumlinge}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/waters area|Kumlinge}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/population density|Kumlinge|round=2}}|PD/km2}}.\n\n{{formatnum: {{pct|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language Swedish|Kumlinge}}|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language total|Kumlinge}}|1}}}} of the population is [[Swedish language|Swedish]]-speaking, {{formatnum: {{pct|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language Finnish|Kumlinge}}|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language total|Kumlinge}}|1}}}} is [[Finnish language|Finnish]]-speaking, and {{formatnum: {{pct|{{#expr: {{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language Sami|Kumlinge}} + {{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language other|Kumlinge}} }}|{{Infobox Finnish municipality/native language total|Kumlinge}}|1}}}} speak other languages.<ref name=\"population_by_language\" /><!-- defined by template:Infobox Finnish Municipality -->\n\nThe [[Kumlinge Airfield]] is situated on the main island.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Kumlinge.jpg|thumb|left|200 px|A milepost in Kumlinge along the [[King's Road (Finland)|King's Road]] showing distances in [[verst]]s to for example [[St Petersburg]], [[Turku]] and [[Helsinki]].]] \nThe first visitors to Kumlinge were [[Vikings]] who stopped there during their voyages. The first permanent residents arrived in the 13th century. According to taxrolls from the 16th century there were about a dozen houses on the main island at the time, home to mostly farmers and fishermen. In the 20th century the population of Kumlinge slowly began to decline.\n\n==Sights==\nThe church in the village is dedicated to [[St. Anne]] and dates from the 15th century. There are two farm museums in Kumlinge: Hermas museig\u00e5rd and Sj\u00f6lunds g\u00e5rdsmuseum. There is also a memorial stone in F\u00e4lberget which is dedicated to the war of 1808 when a Russian [[battalion]] was defeated in the village of Kumlinge. The old post route also goes through Kumlinge. There is also an old but still operational pharmacy on Kumlinge that is well worth a visit with its old inventory.\n\n==Geocaching==\nThere is a growing number of geocaches on Kumlinge that take you to extraordinary places all over the island.\n\n==Demographics==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; margin-left:60px\" \n|- \n!rowspan=1| <center>'''Island'''</center> \n!rowspan=1| <center>'''Population'''</center>\n|- \n|-\n| <center>Kumlinge</center> ||align=left | <center>318</center>\n|-       \n| <center>Enklinge</center> ||align=left | <center>87</center>\n|-\n| <center>Seglinge</center> ||align=left | <center>51</center>\n|-\n| <center>Bj\u00f6rk\u00f6</center> ||align=left | <center>20</center>\n|-\n| <center>Other (e.g. in hospitals) </center> ||align=left | <center>3</center>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Kumlinge}}\n*[http://www.kumlinge.ax/ Municipality of Kumlinge] \u2013 Official website\n*[http://www.kumlinge.ax/component/jce/?view=popup&tmpl=component&img=images/Kartor/kumlinge_kommun.jpg&title= Map of Kumlinge]\n\n[[File:20060808 hermas panorama.jpg|thumb|center|900px|Panorama]]\n\n{{Municipalities of \u00c5land}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of the \u00c5land Islands]]\n\n\n{{\u00c5land-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Finnish municipality\n|name                   = Kumlinge\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|Kumlinges kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area 