y has a population of {{formatnum: {{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|Kronoby}}}} ({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|sourcedate}} }})<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/total area|Kronoby}}|km2}} of which {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/waters area|Kronoby}}|km2|abbr=on}} is water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population density|Kronoby|round=2}}|PD/km2}}.\n\nThe municipality is bilingual, with the majority speaking [[Finland-Swedish|Swedish]] ({{formatnum:{{pct|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/native language Swedish|Kronoby}}|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/native language total|Kronoby}}|1}}}}) and the minority [[Finnish language|Finnish]] ({{formatnum:{{pct|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/native language Finnish|Kronoby}}|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/native language total|Kronoby}}|1}}}}).<ref name=\"population by language\" />\n\n[[Kokkola-Pietarsaari Airport]] is located in Kronoby.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Kronoby}}\n*[http://www.kronoby.fi/ Municipality of Kronoby] \u2013 Official website {{in lang|sv|fi}}\n\n{{ostrobothnia}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of Ostrobothnia (region)]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1607]]\n\n\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Finnish Municipality\n|name                   = Kronoby\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|Kronoby kommun}}<br />{{lang|fi|Kruunupyyn kunta}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = {{lang|sv|Kronoby}} \u2013 {{lang|fi|Kruunupyy}}\n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = Kronoby riverside.jpg\n|